The paper deals with the reduction of decision systems, which is a topic in data mining and falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The use of geometric lattices and matroids is also a common technique in algorithm design and optimization, which falls under the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of these techniques to attribute reduction, which is a problem in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
